description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have excellent IT skills, enjoy working in different locations across Bournemouth and Poole, and love a challenge? We are looking for a full time, adaptable, flexible and enthusiastic individual to join our team as a Community Clinic Support Administrator on a permanent basis to provide day to day administration support for the services using our clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills, an eye for detail and proven IT skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will encompass covering six Community Clinics across Bournemouth and Poole in the absence of the regular Administrator. The main responsibilities of the role will include providing administration support, including audio typing of digital dictations, reception duties, telephone and face to face contact with members of the public, daily contact with clinicians and other professionals, co-ordinating clinic sessions, room bookings, and use of EPR (Electronic Patient Record). It is therefore essential that you are a car driver and hold a driving license. Dorset Healthcare offers a lease car system if you do not currently have access to a car for work purposes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates invited to attend an interview will be required to complete an audio typing test from a digital dictation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time permanent Community Clinic Support Administrator post 37.5 hours per week (Monday to Friday), Band 3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should a large number of applications be received for this post the closing date will be brought forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jen Ward, Community Clinic Support Manager, Email address: jen.ward@nhs.net, Telephone number: 07557634157&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Theakston, Community Clinic Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone Number 07767417304&lt;/p&gt;
